All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

## Summary

### 1. ThemeContext (`context/ThemeContext.tsx`) — Already complete
- Dark/light/system mode with localStorage persistence (`theme-preference`)
- Respects `prefers-color-scheme` as default
- Applies `dark`/`light` class to `<html>`
- Anti-flash inline script in `layout.tsx` `<head>` sets theme before render

### 2. LangContext (`context/LangContext.tsx`) — New file
- PT-BR and EN support with localStorage persistence (`lang` key)
- Detects `navigator.language` as default (pt* → pt, else → en)
- `useLang()` returns `{ t, lang, toggleLang }` where `t` is the full translation tree
- Sets `document.documentElement.lang` attribute

### 3. i18n translations (`lib/data/i18n.ts`) — New file
- Complete bilingual translations for all sections: nav, hero, vision, architecture, methodology, cases, ai, stack, timeline, certifications, insights, contact, footer, chatbot, theme labels, menu labels, loading text
- Added new keys: `hero.name`, `hero.subtitle`, `hero.roles`, `cases.viewSource`, form labels, social labels, `footer.copyright`, chatbot strings, theme/menu aria-labels

### 4. All components updated
- 15 components migrated from `useLanguage()` + `translations[language]` to `useLang()` with `t` object
- Hero, Vision, Architecture, Methodology, Cases, AIExperience, TechStack, Timeline, Certifications, Insights, Contact, Navbar, Footer, SkipLink, AIChatbot — all use the new system
- Hardcoded strings (loading text, aria-labels, error messages) moved to i18n

